title: For Sale:  Arisaka Type 38 WWI
postcontent: For Sale: Arisaka Type 38 6.5 x50mm WWI.  It has the Imperial chrysanthemum, the original bolt & clean bore.  Incredible condition with a very strong action & can still fire.  The value in this piece is not only the condition but the fact in 1914 the Imperial Japanese army decreed all captured weapons need to have the "mum" etched of.  Also, returning soldiers with captured weapons would need to place the bolts in barrels for the voyage home and retrieve at port.  Chance were extremely low to retrieve the original bolt.  I've had this in my collection for awhile and I hope it will find a good home.  Local andf cash sales only.  valid drivers license required and permission to copy and retain with signature proof of firearm transfer.  Thanks for looking
